cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on vehicular ad hoc networks and proposes a protocol for building a multihop transmission backbone network. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses signal attenuation and channel contentions in the dynamic vehicular environment, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper proposes a distributed protocol for building the transmission backbone network. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a distributed protocol for building the transmission backbone network. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a two-tier network architecture and develops a queueing analysis model to evaluate the end-to-end transmission delay and throughput.
